Basic Network Scan
Perform a basic scan for 30 seconds:
sudo python3 wifi_security_analyzer.py -i wlan0 -t 30

Extended Scan with CSV Export
Scan for 2 minutes and save results to a file:
sudo python3 wifi_security_analyzer.py -i wlan0 -t 120 -o scan_results.csv

Security Assessment of Your Network
First, run a scan to discover your network:
sudo python3 wifi_security_analyzer.py -i wlan0 -t 30

Note your network's BSSID from the results, then run a security check:
sudo python3 wifi_security_analyzer.py -i wlan0 -t 30 --check --bssid 00:11:22:33:44:55

Replace 00:11:22:33:44:55 with your actual network's BSSID.

Understanding the Results
The tool provides these key pieces of information:

BSSID: The MAC address of the access point
SSID: The network name
Channel: The Wi-Fi channel being used
Encryption: The security protocol (Open, WEP, WPA, WPA2)
Signal: Signal strength in dBm
Vulnerabilities: Any detected security issues

When running a security check with --check, you'll receive:

Detailed assessment of the network's security
Specific vulnerabilities that were detected
Actionable recommendations to improve security
